<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAZI CONCENTRATION CAMPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On behalf of our editorial staff I strongly object to the use of the phrase 
"Polish concentration camps" in " 'Schindler's List' Breaks the Jinx for 
Spielberg" (Jan. 24). 
</P>
<P>
 There never were any Polish concentration camps, only German concentration 
camps in occupied Poland. This is a critical distinction. This phrase not only 
is inaccurate but also offensive to the Poles and Americans of Polish heritage. 
</P>
<P>
 STANISLAW K. CYBULSKI 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Editor 
</P>
<P>
 Polish Radio Hour 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
 Calendar received numerous calls and letters about use of the phrase.  
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012994-0023 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 008126 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
