<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: READING WORKSHOP SCHEDULED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County parents interested in learning new ways to share the pleasure 
of reading with their children are invited to bring their youngsters to a 
workshop this morning in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by gifted-education associations and a Ventura children's bookstore, 
the workshop will be held from 9 to 11:30 a.m. at Guthrie Hall at Ventura 
College.The cost is $6 per person. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the workshop is open to parents with children of any age, it is 
geared mainly toward students who are 8 to 14 years old and their parents. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will feature two speakers: Robin Rector Krupp, a children's author 
who dresses in costume to present her talks on literature, and bookstore owner 
Jody Fickes. 
</P>
<P>
 In her talk, Krupp will focus on showing parents and children how to create 
their own books. 
</P>
<P>
 Fickes will suggest nonfiction books for children on subjects ranging from 
earthquakes to art. She will also suggest projects that parents and children 
can do together at home, such as simple science experiments, to aid students' 
understanding of nonfiction books. MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
