<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; 5 AIDES TO 
COUNCILMAN SVORINICH CALL IT QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five aides to Los Angeles City Councilman Rudy Svorinich Jr., including his 
longtime friend and chief deputy, John Vidovich, have left his office in what 
Svorinich portrayed as a reorganization but others saw as signs of upheaval 
facing the first-term councilman.  
</P>
<P>
 The resignation of Vidovich, 33, was the first to be announced by Svorinich, 
who was elected last year to succeed longtime Councilwoman Joan Milke Flores in 
the 15th District, which stretches from Watts to San Pedro.Vidovich, a Los 
Angeles city fire captain who was on leave to work for Svorinich, had said he 
would stay two years but decided Jan. 20 to submit his resignation. 
</P>
<P>
 Late Friday, Svorinich announced other resignations after a series of meetings 
with his staff. Others leaving his office will be Wilmington field deputy Lilia 
Fernandez, Harbor City/Harbor Gateway deputy Brian Hannon, senior consultant 
John Barbieri and San Pedro aide Kate Acuna. 
</P>
<P>
 Svorinich did not return repeated phone calls for an interview Friday, but his 
newly hired spokesman, Tom Kruesopon, said the resignations were part of a 
reorganization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
