<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; TRIAL ORDERED IN ALLEGED MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 22-year-old Moorpark man on Friday pleaded not guilty in connection with 
charges that he molested a 12-year-old girl after kidnaping her as she walked 
home from Chaparral Middle school in November. 
</P>
<P>
 A trial date for Robert Magdaleno was set for Feb. 28. 
</P>
<P>
 Magdaleno is charged with five counts of child molestation. According to 
authorities, Magdaleno abducted the girl on Nov. 1 and attacked her in an 
unoccupied home. 
</P>
<P>
 He was arrested several hours after the girl reported the incident. A judge on 
Jan. 14 ordered Magdaleno to stand trial on the charges after ruling that the 
prosecution had enough evidence against him. 
</P>
<P>
 The case been assigned to Superior Court Judge Allan L. Steele, who conducted 
Friday's arraignment. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
