<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRUG POLICY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * At last some of our legislators have discovered what many of their 
constituents have known for quite a while.The "War Against Drugs" has been a 
dismal failure. Prisons are bulging with minor drug offenders, preventing the 
long-term incarceration of perpetrators of serious crimes. 
</P>
<P>
 Drug addiction should be viewed as a medical and a social problem. Let us hope 
that the National Coalition for Drug Policy Change and the surgeon general 
continue to seek solutions to a complex problem. 
</P>
<P>
 DOROTHY CHAPMAN 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 
</P>
