<HEADLINE>
<P>
HE'S HAPPY TO SEE 'NAILS' NAILED BY AGENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Congratulations to sports agent Alan Meersand for firing Lenny Dykstra, the 
poorest excuse for a human being I've ever met.It's time such egomaniacal 
athletes experience a dose of reality. Mr. Meersand deserves a purple heart for 
his past pain and suffering. 
</P>
<P>
 Dykstra humiliated me with his ignorant insults and profanity in front of 
co-workers, customers and management when I worked as a waiter at the Pacific 
Dining Car in Los Angeles. He also falsely accused me of stealing his credit 
card, for which I was exonerated by Dykstra's teammate, who later attempted to 
apologize for his behavior. Dykstra, a New York Met at the time, never bothered 
to do so. 
</P>
<P>
 JAMES A. VAUGHN 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 
</P>
