<HEADLINE>
<P>
IS ELLIS WORTH MORE THAN THE MILLIONAIRES? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was deeply moved by the article about Harold Ellis by Chris Baker (Jan. 
25).If there are any parents in search of a role model for their child, I would 
hope they consider the following: 
</P>
<P>
 -- Harold Ellis makes $150,000 per year or $1,829 per game. He gives 100% 
full-time effort and is ecstatic about being with the Clippers. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Ron Harper makes $4 million this year or $48,780 per game, gives 100% 
part-time effort, blasts his employer and is miserably unhappy playing for the 
Clippers. 
</P>
<P>
 Surely I'm missing something here. 
</P>
<P>
 RICHARD BOURICIUS 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 
</P>
