<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRVINE DANCER GETS SPOT ON ARTS ROSTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Arts Council on Thursday granted East Indian dancer Ramya 
Harishankar of Irvine a spot on its Touring Artists Directory for 1995-97. 
Those who present artists on the roster are eligible for partial fee subsidies 
from the CAC. 
</P>
<P>
 The council, meeting at the Bowers Museum, also announced that it will extend 
by two weeks Tuesday's deadline for certain grant applicants in Los Angeles 
County affected by the Northridge earthquake. The extension applies to 
educational, service and multidisciplinary performing-presenting and visual 
arts organizations. 
</P>
<P>
 Touring troupes listed on the council's current Touring Artists Directory that 
had to reschedule performances because of the earthquake will be covered under 
their existing contracts, as will any artists-in-residence forced to postpone 
their presentations, the council announced.ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
