<P>
GAS LEAK IN COLOMBIA KILLS 3, POISONS 300 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A gas leak in Colombia's third-largest city killed three people and poisoned 
at least 300 Friday, causing widespread panic as residents scrambled to escape 
to cleaner air. 
</P>
<P>
 The disaster occurred around midnight in four neighborhoods in east Cali, 185 
miles southwest of Bogota. 
</P>
<P>
 Chloride gas in the underground sewage system seeped into homes as most 
residents slept, said Gen. Jose Reyes, commander of Cali's police department. 
</P>
