<HEADLINE>
<P>
GROSS, MARTINEZ GET INCREASES, AGREE TO '94 DODGER CONTRACTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pitchers Kevin Gross and Ramon Martinez got substantial raises Friday as the 
Dodgers avoided arbitration hearings. 
</P>
<P>
 Gross agreed to a one-year contract worth $2.7 million, up from his 
three-year, $6.4 million deal that ran out after last season. Gross, 32, was 
13-13 with a 4.14 earned-run average last season and had asked for $3 million 
in arbitration. 
</P>
<P>
 Martinez, 25, agreed to a one-year deal worth $2,687,500 after a 10-12 season 
in which he had a 3.44 ERA and three shutouts in 32 starts. He had sought $2.9 
million after earning $1,775,000 last season. 
