SOCCER; DILUTED TEAM OF RUSSIANS TO PLAY U.S. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. national soccer team, off to a 1-0-1 start in 1994, will play host to 
a Russian team of unknown quality tonight at the Kingdome. 
</P>
<P>
 For the U.S. team, the game will be a chance to simulate conditions for its 
first World Cup game, June 18 in the Silverdome at Pontiac, Mich. 
</P>
<P>
 Under different circumstances, the game against Russia would be an opportunity 
for the Americans to test themselves against a World Cup qualifier. But the 
Russian team is in disarray because of a player boycott. More than half the 
players on the national roster have not reported to a training camp. They are 
calling for the removal of Coach Pavel Sadyrin. JULIE CART 
