<P>
QUAKE RELIEF IS WINNER AS SOLIS HAS A BIG DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alex Solis' big day Friday at Santa Anita was the American Red Cross' gain. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier in the week, the meeting's leading rider announced he would donate his 
Friday earnings to earthquake relief. 
</P>
<P>
 He rode four winners. 
</P>
<P>
 Solis won the first race with favored Trusting Heart, then swept the final 
three with Ms. Something, Service Ace and Uncanny Ann. He also had a third and 
a fourth on the afternoon, so his total donation to the Red Cross was $6,950. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was (trainer) Mel Stute's idea," Solis said. "I was at his barn on 
Wednesday morning and I walked in and he said, 'How you doing, son?' and I told 
him, 'I'm having a good time riding horses and everything's going well and I 
just feel so fortunate that everything is going so well.' 
</P>
<P>
 "I told him I couldn't believe that I'm having so much fun and making so much 
money and he suggested I donate some of it (to earthquake relief). I said it 
sounded like a good idea. 
</P>
<P>
 "It really feels good to make such a donation. I was very excited all week 
long to do it and I couldn't wait until today to see how everything was going 
to work out. Every day I pray to God I come out healthy, and for all the other 
jockeys, too. Today, I prayed that everybody came out healthy and that my 
horses ran well, too." 
</P>
<P>
 Harry Haceck, Solis' agent, also donated his share of the rider's earnings. 
BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
