<HEADLINE>
<P>
TURKISH, PAKISTANI LEADERS TO VISIT WAR-TORN BOSNIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The prime ministers of Turkey and Pakistan will visit Sarajevo to call 
attention to the plight of the Bosnian people, it was announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Turkish Prime Minister Tansu Ciller and Pakistani leader Benazir Bhutto will 
make the visit "as two concerned stateswomen and mothers," a statement from 
Ciller's office said. 
