<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; NO. 1 MATER DEI HAS NO TROUBLE KEEPING RECORD 
UNBLEMISHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Clay McKnight scored 21 points, including five three-pointers, and Schea 
Cotton scored 20 as top-ranked Mater Dei defeated Dana Hills, 78-45, in a South 
Coast League boys' basketball game Friday night at Dana Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Miles Simon added 14 points for the Monarchs (23-0, 7-0), who led, 40-17, at 
halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Donald Meyers led Dana Hills (11-11, 4-3) with 18 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In other South Coast League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 77, El Toro 54 -- John Earnest scored 18 points, and Brandon 
Puffer added 11 for host Capistrano Valley (15-7, 4-3), which made 10 
three-point baskets. 
</P>
<P>
 Twelve of Capistrano Valley's 14 players scored. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Bone led El Toro (10-12, 2-5) with 11 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo 62, San Clemente 61 -- Freshman Austin Moherman hit two 
free-throws with 17 seconds left to clinch the game for host Mission Viejo 
(9-11, 3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente's Luke Mannix made a three-pointer with eight seconds left, but 
San Clemente was unable to gain possession again. 
</P>
<P>
 Jerry Reid scored 19 points for Mission Viejo, while Garrett Sleichter scored 
17 for San Clemente (10-12, 1-6). 
</P>
