<HEADLINE>
<P>
ISLAS ELIGIBLE FOR SANTA ANA VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley soccer player Francisco Islas, whose age was questioned by 
Orange High, was declared eligible Friday by Santa Ana Valley Principal Robert 
Nelson.Islas, a Times All-County player last year, received a birth certificate 
Friday that indicated he was born in 1976, making him 17 years old. 
Administrators at Orange High had claimed Islas was born in 1974. 
</P>
<P>
 Karen Hellyer, a Southern Section administrator, said: "(Santa Ana Valley) 
apparently has verified that the kid is 17 years old. They're going to be 
forwarding that information to the office." 
</P>
<P>
 Islas, who has scored 11 goals this season, had missed Valley's last six games 
while his eligibility was being questioned. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012994-0170 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 008273 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
