<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; GOLDEN WEST BEATS RIVERSIDE TO KEEP 
VICTORY STREAKS ALIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden West, ranked second in the state, barely kept its home and Orange 
Empire Conference winning streaks alive Friday with a 71-70 victory over 
Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside, which made 10 of 20 three-point attempts, cut the lead to 71-70 on 
a three-pointer by Virginia Vaioletama with 23 seconds left.Riverside got the 
ball back with six seconds remaining but couldn't get a shot. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the 24th consecutive conference victory and the 65th in a row at home 
for Golden West (25-3, 7-0).  
</P>
<P>
 Deana Itow had 23 points, and Katie Miner added 22 for the Rustlers. Miner was 
scoreless in Golden West's 65-55 victory over Fullerton Wednesday. She was nine 
of 10 from the field Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Itow and Michelle Kravic also had 13 rebounds each for Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
 Audrey McMurry had 20 points and eight rebounds for Riverside (20-9, 3-4), the 
ninth-ranked team in the state. 
</P>
<P>
 In other conference games: 
</P>
