<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; OKENWA LEADS MASTER'S TO 73-70 COMEBACK WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Emeka Okenwa scored a game-high 25 points -- including 16 in the second half 
-- to power The Master's College to a 73-70 come-from-behind victory over host 
Cal State Dominguez Hills in a nonconference men's basketball game Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the ninth victory in a row for the Mustangs (20-3), their 16th in 17 
games, and their seventh in nine games this season against teams from the 
California Collegiate Athletic Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Dominguez Hills (12-7) took an early 15-2 lead, but Master's narrowed its 
deficit to 35-31 at halftime and took the lead for good when Okenwa hit a jump 
shot from the left baseline to give the Mustangs a 59-58 advantage with 5 1/2 
minutes left. BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Hoover 55, Crescenta Valley 54 -- Andreh Allaharyan scored with two seconds 
remaining to give Hoover the upset in a Pacific League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Allaharyan led all scorers with 23 points. Brock Jacobsen scored 20 points for 
Crescenta Valley (13-8. 3-4). Hoover improved to 8-13, 1-6. 
</P>
