League victory. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Francis 66, Bishop Amat 53 -- Chris Ott, a 6-11 senior, scored 15 points 
to lead St. Francis (16-5, 7-1) in a Del Rey League game at Bishop Amat. 
</P>
<P>
 Mihail Papadopulos, Dan Bir and Tim Murphy each had 12 points for St. Francis. 
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 La Verne 71, Cal Lutheran 60 -- Cal Lutheran led at the half despite hitting 
only one of its first 21 field-goal tries, but was unable to hold on in the 
second half. Guard Tiffany Hall scored 25 points and had five steals and 
teammate Rachell Auld added 22 points and 12 rebounds for the Regals. GIRLS' 
BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley 86, Hoover 25 -- Sarah Hagman scored 35 points to lead the 
Falcons' rout of Hoover (3-14, 3-4) in a Pacific League game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Falcons (16-5, 6-1) led, 25-8, after the first quarter. Stephanie Labor 
recorded her fifth triple-double of the season, with 13 points, 10 rebounds and 
10 assists. Sara Strother added 23 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Nordhoff 67, Moorpark 49 -- Senior Rachel McSorley scored 19 points to lead 
the host Rangers (16-3, 5-0) in a Frontier league game. Thy Nguyen paced 
Moorpark (5-12, 2-3) with 21 points. BOYS' SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 7, Nordhoff 1 -- Pat Russo scored a hat trick and Curtis Silverest 
added two goals in Moorpark's 15th straight victory. 
</P>
<P>
 With the match tied, 1-1, Moorpark (20-2, 5-0) scored six times in the second 
half. GIRLS' SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 La Reina 3, Bishop Diego 1 -- Michelle Nuesca had two goals and one assist and 
Sami Conroy scored the other goal, keeping La Reina undefeated in the 
Tri-Valley league. 
