<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; SPEECH WILL KICK OFF FESTIVAL OF WHALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Peter Burtchell of the Cousteau Society will kick off the city's Festival of 
Whales with a speech titled "Threats to Our Global Ocean" at 7 p.m. Feb. 25 at 
Dana Hills High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Burtchell will be joined, via satellite from Belize, by Robert Ballard, who 
discovered the R.M.S. Titanic.Their presentation will focus on how the 
exploitation of the ocean is changing our lifestyle. 
</P>
<P>
 They will also offer solutions and opportunities for individual action to make 
the world safer. 
</P>
<P>
 Donations of $15 per person, or $25 for special seats, are requested. The 
money will benefit the Orange County Marine Institute, Dana Hills High School 
and the Monarch Beach Sunrise Rotary's Village Bank project in Belize. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (800) 290-DANA; to charge tickets by phone, call 
(714) 248-2871. 
