<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAYE CLARK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The United Synagogue of Conservative Judaism announced that a National 
Disaster Relief Fund will be created to assist communities during natural 
disasters. Working through Conservative congregations in the affected areas, 
the fund will distribute grants to institutions and individuals whose losses 
would not be covered by standard insurance policies. 
</P>
<P>
 This is a joint project of the Federation of Jewish Men's Clubs, the Jewish 
Theological Seminary of America, the Rabbinical Assembly, the United Synagogue 
and Women's League for Conservative Judaism. Information: (212) 533-7800. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County Religion Notes is published on Saturdays. Send the item at least 
two weeks before the event to Orange County Religion Notes, The Times, 1375 
Sunflower Ave., Costa Mesa, Calif. 92626. Telephone calls cannot be accepted. 
Because of space limitations, The Times cannot guarantee that all notices will 
be published. Items must include subject, telephone number, event date, time 
and exact address. 
</P>
